{"answer_uniqueness_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"artifact_id":"q-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","artifact_type":"question","author":{"identity":"openai-codex-sap-org-04-content-author","identity_type":"model","role":"lesson_question_author"},"blueprint_references":[{"blueprint_id":"aws-sap-c02-assessment-blueprint","canonical_digest":"3362d465a410c84d40250cd3b6dcfa5ac80cfc25d0b8d7b034b45327b8049d8d","version":"0.3A.1"}],"canonical_digest":"35b1f38296119ccd2e48b554c6a09f4777c0d46e062da88e8732e60c23f9feba","content_review_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"created_at":"2026-07-19T21:30:00Z","keyed_option_ids":["a"],"learner_explanation":"Option A is best. An owner can share a subnet that is not in a default VPC through AWS RAM with accounts or OUs in the same AWS Organization. The platform account retains ownership, the RAM permission is a ceiling, consumer identities still need applicable allows, and consumers use the Regional resource in its owner-account Region. Separate VPCs and subnets violate the ownership and overhead requirements. A broad administrator role does not implement the scoped resource-share model, and a Regional subnet is not accessed as a global resource.","modified_at":"2026-07-20T04:13:00Z","objective_references":{"primary":"SAP-ORG-04","supporting":["SAP-FND-01","SAP-FND-02","SAP-ORG-02"]},"option_rationales":[{"category":"key_support","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-vpc-subnet-shareable","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c4754689803fa189b0971486dbec48f51a06f88d6d748029c4a60afec6a8a23f","revision":3}],"is_keyed":true,"option_id":"a","rationale":"It uses the approved sharing path for an eligible subnet and satisfies ownership, OU targeting, layered permission, Region, and overhead requirements.","requirement_ids":["req-owner","req-scope","req-access","req-overhead"]},{"category":"excessive_operational_burden","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-vpc-subnet-shareable","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c4754689803fa189b0971486dbec48f51a06f88d6d748029c4a60afec6a8a23f","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"b","rationale":"Separate VPCs and subnets would be owned and administered in each application account, recreating the administration and ownership distribution the scenario asks to avoid.","requirement_ids":["req-owner","req-overhead"]},{"category":"wrong_security_boundary","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"c","rationale":"A broad administrator role is not the scoped RAM share and permission model required by the scenario.","requirement_ids":["req-scope","req-access"]},{"category":"unstated_assumption","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-vpc-subnet-shareable","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c4754689803fa189b0971486dbec48f51a06f88d6d748029c4a60afec6a8a23f","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"d","rationale":"The option assumes global access that the approved Regional-resource behavior does not provide.","requirement_ids":["req-access"]}],"options":[{"option_id":"a","text":"Create an AWS RAM resource share for the subnet, target the selected OU, choose the appropriate RAM permission, and grant consumer identities only the required operations."},{"option_id":"b","text":"Create a separate VPC and subnet in every application account and let each team own and administer its copy."},{"option_id":"c","text":"Grant a broad cross-account administrator role into the platform account instead of creating a resource share."},{"option_id":"d","text":"Create an AWS RAM resource share for the subnet, target the selected OU in one Region, and require consumers to access the subnet from any Region as though it were global."}],"originality_review_state":{"review":null,"status":"pending"},"question_id":"q-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","question_type":"single_response","required_selection_count":1,"requirement_option_matrix":[{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-owner"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-scope"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"fails"}],"requirement_id":"req-access"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-overhead"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"not_applicable"},{"option_id":"c","result":"not_applicable"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"con-supported"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"not_applicable"},{"option_id":"c","result":"not_applicable"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"con-org"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"c","result":"not_applicable"},{"option_id":"d","result":"fails"}],"requirement_id":"con-region"}],"revision":6,"schema_version":"ala.authoring.question.v1","source_citation_projection":[{"canonical_digest":"40ade314f1a81ccd854f670963fa5b08f5ea88b6424348895b45f2206547e694","locator":"How resource sharing works; What is AWS Resource Access Manager?","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-ram-overview"},{"canonical_digest":"cb36a0e0a212531d835e7f2462f72370e097b3641c7f23ae4555fe8ce275e2a9","locator":"Enable resource sharing within AWS Organizations > Requirements and Important","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-ram-sharing"},{"canonical_digest":"2f90f78b228cd903c1622a6bf9f28edce2380ee5f023628f0f12e4b8581ffeca","locator":"VPC resources > Subnets","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-vpc-subnet-limitations"},{"canonical_digest":"7e7c803a6bf852a9660ed0a210b694a4c389af1d7d4ca2b5c0e2785cd8f93325","locator":"Share your VPC subnets with other accounts; Shared subnet prerequisites; Working with shared subnets > Share a subnet","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-vpc-subnet-sharing"}],"specification_reference":{"artifact_id":"qspec-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","artifact_type":"question_spec","canonical_digest":"e528d3b9f8c2628bb212c9933806cd30d48d8b05319c10ffd5b382da4d433761","revision":4},"status":"active","stem":"A platform account owns an Amazon VPC subnet that is not in a default VPC. Application accounts in a selected OU of the same AWS Organization must use the shared subnet in the Region where it exists. Organization sharing is enabled through AWS RAM. The platform team must retain ownership, consumer actions must remain limited by both the share and consumer identity permissions, and the company wants to avoid creating a separate VPC and subnet in every application account. Which design best meets these requirements?","supersedes":{"artifact_id":"q-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","artifact_type":"question","canonical_digest":"c409f607813d12aa57de424a727e5d0aeba76aa2155890c8985398d0b5061dce","revision":5},"supporting_claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-vpc-subnet-shareable","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c4754689803fa189b0971486dbec48f51a06f88d6d748029c4a60afec6a8a23f","revision":3}],"validation_state":{"report":null,"status":"not_run"}}
